Neptune is direct later today! Yay!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Neptune retrograde brought plenty of reality checks, including a few unpleasant ones. But now we can dream of a better world. Hope is returning, and we can find faith in the future.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Art, music, intuition, spirituality - it's all flowing beautifully. The shadow side of Neptune is escapism. While there is nothing wrong with wanting to lose yourself in dreamworld, you don't want to ignore what's happening. Stay grounded.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
PS Neptune will be locked in a square to the Sun from December 8th - 18th. During this period, it's way too easy to scatter your forces to the wind. You'll also want to remain on high alert for deception, gaslighting, and general flakiness. The more alert you are, the more likely you'll skate through that window like Johnny Weir on fresh ice. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#astrology #coveryourasstrology #thetarotlady #neptunedirect

Practical thinking is IN when Mercury waltzes into Capricorn on the 6th for a nice long stay. During this transit, it’s easier than ever to create order. The Full Moon in Gemini 2022 happens on Wednesday, December 7th, at 11:08 PM EST. Here are some Full Moon in Gemini mini tarot readings with the Unifying Consciousness Tarot!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Aries: 10 of Pentacles - There are so many things going right for you now. Focus on that - and your blessings will multiply.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Taurus: Mind of Pentacles - What do you want the most? You can manifest it - if you believe in yourself. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Gemini: Hanged One reversed - Nothing can bind you any longer. The gestation period is over. You are free to go - and grow.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Cancer: Judgement - A major awakening is on the way. You can see the light - and burn away all the old crap once and for all.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Leo: Ace of Swords - It's time to move on your ideas. Take action on your brightest ones - and you'll see new levels of success.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Virgo: The Sun - At last, the Universe is turning in your favor. It seemed like it would never happen - but your moment is HERE. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Libra: Ace of Cups - This marks a turning point in your emotional life. Put the old stories behind you. Begin writing a new one.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Scorpio: 3 of Wands reversed - Some situations are on hold. That doesn't mean they won't happen. Trust your timing.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Sagittarius: 9 of Pentacles - Look at you flourishing and succeeding in everything you do! All the stars are aligned for your benefit.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Capricorn: Mind of Swords - The only one who can master your thoughts is YOU. Clear away the mental clutter, and you'll see the truth.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Aquarius: Soul of Wands - A situation requires boldness. No more waiting around. Step forward with confidence and watch what happens.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Pisces: 3 of Pentacles - You have so much help around you at this time. That support helps you pull off a miracle. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

The cosmos is ready to get down to spiritual business when Saturn swims into Pisces on the 7th. This transit is fantastic for connecting with something greater than yourself. Dedicate yourself to regular spiritual practices, and you can experience a profound inner change. It’s also divine for artists, writers, and musicians. If you fall into one of those categories, you might finish a major piece of work. Think of this as inspiration meeting discipline – the perfect combo for making magic! Of course, this could also work in your favor if you want to manifest a big vision goal. What you dream of can become a reality if you commit.

With all the Saturn energy happening today, you might hear some astrologers talking about the Saturn return, an astrological event that happens every 27 years or so. In a nutshell: this occurs when transiting Saturn moves back into the same sign it was when you were born and signals a time of new maturity. For example, if Saturn was in Pisces when you were born, now that the ringed planet has entered Pisces, you're in your Saturn return!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Most astrologers focus on the first Saturn return, but did you know there are three? Each one is important.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The first happens around ages 27 - 30. This marks your official entry into adulthood. It's time to get serious and responsible for the life you want to create.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The second occurs around ages 57 - 60. Now you've reached the pinnacle of your career and can begin to prepare for retirement. This transition is into the role of the wise elder. What will your legacy be?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The third Saturn return happens around ages 85 - 80. This is your time to prepare for the final journey. What stories do you want to leave behind? Have you crossed items off your bucket list? This is your spiritual graduation and a time to let go of what is no longer essential.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
You can learn more about Saturn return and other important transits (Solar return, Uranus aspects, Jupiter return, etc) in my latest book, Twist Your Fate: Manifest Success with Astrology and Tarot. Available wherever books are sold, online and off.

We are not always dealt the gentlest cards in life. Sometimes we’re dealt a very difficult hand. At some point, all of us will be confronted by life’s inevitable tough passages: the loss of loved ones, a health crisis or illness, the endless thrum of national and global tragedies—as well as the empty nest, the loss of a job, the loss of a relationship, the loss of youth.

When we’re going through a difficult time, tarot can be a source of comfort, catharsis, healing, and connection to a power greater than ourselves. And when you realize, “I have three options, and frankly, all of them are lousy and this whole situation is just really sad,” tarot can help you find acceptance and bear the pain with a little more grace.

But even in difficult times, we can find purpose and hope. With tarot as a tool, we can make wiser choices and steer things in a more positive direction.

Grief is something that touches all of us at one time or another. I’ve been there. I know grief well.

Join me here on Instagram Live for 7 days to talk about how to handle grief in better, healthier ways. Because here’s the deal: everyone is grieving something, or will be, or knows someone who is. 

We need to normalize talking about it instead of sweeping it away like an inconvenient mess. 

In this mini-series, we’ll talk about:
What is good grief versus unhealthy grief
Self-care
What to say (and not to say) to someone who is grieving
When you’re not okay
And more

I’ll share easy tarot practices to help you move through tender times. (Yes, tarot can be a helpful tool. I'll show you!)

Bring your favorite tarot deck, a journal, and whatever makes you feel comfy.
